Add a public function called HandleResult to Calculator.calr that processes a Result<i32, str> and returns the value or -1 on error. It takes Result<i32,str> parameter res and returns i32.

Use this exact Calor Result matching syntax:
§F{f003:HandleResult:pub}
  §I{Result<i32,str>:res}
  §O{i32}
  §R §W{w001} res
    §K §OK §VAR{v} → v
    §K §ERR §VAR{e} → (- 0 1)
  §/W{w001}
§/F{f003}

The Result pattern matching syntax:
- §OK §VAR{v} matches Ok and binds the success value to v
- §ERR §VAR{e} matches Err and binds the error value to e
- Use these with §K in a switch expression
- §R §W{...} returns the result of the switch expression
